SCENARIO 1: Web Application Not Loading (Permission Denied)

A company hosts a website on Apache/Nginx.
Application returns:

403 Forbidden
Permission denied: /var/www/html

Reason

The web server user (apache, nginx, www-data) doesnâ€™t have permission.

Fix
sudo chown -R apache:apache /var/www/html
sudo chmod -R 755 /var/www/html

Why it happens

Developers deploy files, but ownership gets changed accidentally.

