Real impact

Build pipeline stops â†’ deployment blocked â†’ production release delayed.

ğŸŸ§ ğŸ”µ SCENARIO 3: Developer Needs Access Without Changing Owner

A developer from the AI team needs access to a file managed by the Linux admin team.
Ownership cannot be changed.

Solution using ACL
setfacl -m u:rahul:rw /data/report.csv

Why real companies use this

Multiple teams may need access â†’ ACL gives fine-grained permission.

ğŸŸ¨ ğŸ”µ SCENARIO 4: Shared Team Folder Keeps Overwriting Group Ownership

Team folder /project/data/ is used by DevOps team.
New files created inside become owned by â€œrootâ€ group instead of â€œdevopsâ€.

Fix using SGID bit
chgrp -R devops /project/data
chmod 2775 /project/data

Meaning of 2 (SGID)

Files inside inherit the group.

Real reason

Prevents permission issues in shared environments.

ğŸŸ¥ ğŸ”µ SCENARIO 5: A User Cannot Delete Files in Shared Folder

Folder: /shared/logs/
Users get:

Operation not permitted

Reason: sticky bit missing
Fix
chmod +t /shared/logs

Where companies use sticky bit?

/tmp

Shared project folders

Jenkins workspace

ğŸŸª ğŸ”µ SCENARIO 6: Application Logs Not Getting Created

App fails to write logs in /var/log/app/:

Error writing log file

Reason

Folder owned by root.

Fix
sudo chown -R appuser:appgroup /var/log/app
chmod -R 750 /var/log/app

In real companies

Logging issues break monitoring (Prometheus/ELK).

ğŸŸ« ğŸ”µ SCENARIO 7: Security Team Requires Sensitive File Protection

Company must store credentials/keys with restricted access.

Solution:
chmod 600 secrets.key
chown root:root secrets.key

Why?

Only root should read the file â†’ standard security practice.

ğŸŸ¦ ğŸ”µ SCENARIO 8: File Has â€˜immutableâ€™ Attribute â€” Cannot Delete or Edit

Admin tries:

rm -f config.conf


Gets:

Operation not permitted

Reason

File attribute immutable.

Check
lsattr config.conf

Remove
chattr -i config.conf
rm config.conf

Real company example

Immutable protects important configs like /etc/resolv.conf.

ğŸŸ© ğŸ”µ SCENARIO 9: Database Backup Fails Due to Permission Issues

MySQL backup script writes to /backup/db/.

Error:

