ğŸŸ§ ğŸ”µ SCENARIO 10: Docker Container Cannot Read Host Files

Container mounts:

/data:/app/data

Inside container:

permission denied

Reason

Host directory not owned properly.

Fix
sudo chown -R 1000:1000 /data
chmod 755 /data

Real-world usage

Containers run as non-root â†’ need correct UID/GID mapping.

ğŸ”µ COMMON INTERVIEW QUESTIONS (REAL COMPANY INTERVIEWS)
1ï¸âƒ£ How do you give permission to only the owner?
chmod 700 folder

2ï¸âƒ£ What is sticky bit?

Only the owner can delete files in a shared folder.

Set:

chmod +t /shared

3ï¸âƒ£ What is the difference between 644, 755, and 775?

644 â†’ owner read+write, others read

755 â†’ owner rwx, others r-x (common for web apps)

775 â†’ owner & group rwx, others r-x

4ï¸âƒ£ What is ACL and why is it needed?

ACL = fine-grained permission system.
Used when multiple users need different access.

5ï¸âƒ£ How do you check all permissions (including ACL & attributes)?
ls -l
getfacl file
lsattr file

6ï¸âƒ£ How do you give multiple users access to a directory?
setfacl -m u:alice:rwx -m u:bob:rw /data

7ï¸âƒ£ How do you protect critical configuration files?
chattr +i /etc/ssh/sshd_config

8ï¸âƒ£ What is the SGID bit?

Ensures all files inherit group ownership.
